    • Method Detail

      • addHistoryFromGosu

        HistoryCoreExt addHistoryFromGosu(java.util.Date eventDate,
                                HistoryEventType type,
                                java.lang.String description,
                                Transaction transaction,
                                java.lang.String refNumber,
                                java.lang.Boolean countsAsActivity)
        This method is meant to be called directly from gosu to generate history events.

        To add a history event from java code instead of from gosu, call the other addHistory methods available on this class

        Parameters:
        eventDate - the timestamp that should be associated with the History event
        type - HistoryEventType typekey corresponding to the type of History event (eg: trouble ticket created)
        description - a text description for the History event
        transaction - Transaction associated with History event (or null if there is no relevant transaction)
        refNumber - String displayed in the UI as "reference number" of the History event (or null if there isn't a relevant ref number)
        countsAsActivity - this history event counts as activity
        Returns:
        newly created History event
